    <sectiondef kind="user-defined">
      <header>RTC Interface Update</header>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__rtc__interface_1ga0b2b2b44077dcdb73feb007f87cc47b3" prot="public" static="yes" const="no" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>int</type>
        <definition>static int rtc_update_set_callback</definition>
        <argsstring>(const struct device *dev, rtc_update_callback callback, void *user_data)</argsstring>
        <name>rtc_update_set_callback</name>
        <param>
          <type>const struct <ref refid="structdevice" kindref="compound">device</ref> *</type>
          <declname>dev</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="group__rtc__interface_1ga9d3eb555ac4ad86b7ff66d359652a29e" kindref="member">rtc_update_callback</ref></type>
          <declname>callback</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>void *</type>
          <declname>user_data</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>API for setting update callback. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Setting the update callback will enable the update callback. The update callback will be invoked every time the RTC clock is updated by 1 second. It can be used to synchronize the RTC clock with other clock sources.</para>
<para>To disable the update callback for the RTC clock, the <computeroutput>callback</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>user_data</computeroutput> parameters must be set to NULL.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>dev</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Device instance </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>callback</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Callback called when update occurs </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>user_data</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Optional user data passed to callback</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 if successful </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>-ENOTSUP if API is not supported by hardware </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>-errno code if failure </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/drivers/rtc.h" line="466" column="19" bodyfile="zephyr/drivers/rtc.h" bodystart="466" bodyend="474"/>
      </memberdef>
